('Google SRE Four Golden Signals Applied to MOTHER v74.x',
'The Four Golden Signals (Beyer et al., Google SRE Book Ch.6, 2016) applied to MOTHER: (1) Latency — target p95 < 8000ms for streaming responses; current baseline unknown due to missing reliabilityLogger.recordQuery() calls in core.ts. (2) Traffic — queries per minute; visible in MOTHER interface as "Mensagens: 0" per session. (3) Errors — target < 1% error rate; DGM proposal failures inflate this metric. (4) Saturation — Cloud Run max instances and memory limits. The reliability monitor (ReliabilityMonitor.tsx + /api/reliability-metrics SSE endpoint) was implemented in v74.9 but lacks real data because core.ts does not yet call reliabilityLogger.recordQuery() after each query. This is the highest-priority remaining action for v74.10: add reliabilityLogger.recordQuery() call in core.ts processQuery() function.',
