-- TypeScript union type safety
('TypeScript Union Types and Literal Types for AI System Safety',
'TypeScript literal union types (e.g., type LogComponent = "guardian" | "crag" | "core" | "system") provide compile-time guarantees that AI system components only emit logs with valid component identifiers. This prevents silent failures where a misspelled component name causes logs to be miscategorized or dropped. In MOTHER v74.8, fitness_scorer.ts used "fitness" as a LogComponent which is not in the union — TypeScript caught this at compile time (TS2345). The fix is to use "system" as the fallback component for modules not in the primary component list, or to add "fitness" to the LogComponent union type. The latter is preferable for observability: adding "fitness" to the union allows the reliability monitor to filter logs by component. Scientific basis: TypeScript Handbook "Literal Types" (Microsoft, 2024); Pierce (2002) "Types and Programming Languages" — type safety as a correctness guarantee.',
'TypeScript Handbook (Microsoft, 2024) "Literal Types"; Pierce (2002) "Types and Programming Languages" MIT Press',
'engineering',
'["typescript", "union-types", "literal-types", "type-safety", "log-component"]',
NOW(), NOW()),

-- Property-based testing exclusion from production builds
('Excluding Test Files from Production TypeScript Builds',
'Test files (*.test.ts, *.spec.ts) that import test-only dependencies (fast-check, better-sqlite3, vitest) must be excluded from the production TypeScript build configuration. The tsconfig.json root config already excluded **/*.test.ts but not **/*.spec.ts. The tsconfig.server.json did not exclude test files at all. Cloud Build uses `npx tsc --noEmit` which uses the root tsconfig.json — this includes server/**/* which includes server/mother.property.test.ts. Since fast-check and better-sqlite3 are devDependencies not installed in the production Docker image, the type check fails. Fix: add "**/*.test.ts" and "**/*.spec.ts" to the exclude array in both tsconfig.json and tsconfig.server.json. This is the standard pattern for monorepo TypeScript projects with separate test and production configs. Scientific basis: TypeScript Project References documentation (Microsoft, 2024); Jest/Vitest best practices for TypeScript.',
'TypeScript Handbook "Project References" (Microsoft, 2024); Vitest documentation "TypeScript" (2024)',
'engineering',
'["typescript", "tsconfig", "test-exclusion", "production-build", "vitest", "fast-check"]',
NOW(), NOW());
